RN   [1]
RP   NUCLEOTIDE SEQUENCE [GENOMIC DNA].
RC   STRAIN=27655-3B;
RX   PubMed=8550497; DOI=10.1128/jb.178.3.662-667.1996;
RA   Collinson S.K., Clouthier S.C., Doran J.L., Banser P.A., Kay W.W.;
RT   "Salmonella enteritidis agfBAC operon encoding thin, aggregative
RT   fimbriae.";
RL   J. Bacteriol. 178:662-667(1996).
RN   [2]
RP   PROTEIN SEQUENCE OF N-TERMINUS, FUNCTION IN THIN AGGREGATIVE FIMBRIAE
RP   ASSEMBLY, SUBCELLULAR LOCATION, DISRUPTION PHENOTYPE, INDUCTION, AND
RP   OPERON STRUCTURE.
RC   STRAIN=27655-3B;
RX   PubMed=17379722; DOI=10.1099/mic.0.2006/000935-0;
RA   Gibson D.L., White A.P., Rajotte C.M., Kay W.W.;
RT   "AgfC and AgfE facilitate extracellular thin aggregative fimbriae
RT   synthesis in Salmonella enteritidis.";
RL   Microbiology 153:1131-1140(2007).
CC   -!- FUNCTION: Plays a role in the extracellular assembly of CsgA (also
CC       known as AgfA, AC P0A1E7) into thin aggregative fimbriae (Tafi)
CC       fibers. Assembly may also require CsgE (AgfE). Tafi are thought to
CC       be assembled via an extracellular nucleation-precipitation (ENP)
CC       pathway, and possibly also via an intracellular non-CsgC-dependent
CC       pathway. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:17379722}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Periplasm {ECO:0000269|PubMed:17379722}.
CC       Note=Upon overexpression; a small amount is also seen in the
CC       cytoplasm.
CC   -!- INDUCTION: Expressed at low levels in agar-grown cells, part of
CC       the csgBAC (agfBAC) operon. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:17379722}.
CC   -!- DISRUPTION PHENOTYPE: Cells lacking this gene make aberrant thin
CC       aggregative fimbriae (Tafi) which are composed solely of CsgA.
CC       Normal Tafi are composed of CsgA and CsgB at a 20:1 ration.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:17379722}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the CsgC/AgfC family. {ECO:0000305}.

CC   Distributed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivs License
